    And<T>
    A Predicate that is a conjunction of a list of others.

    A wrapper for objects so they are compared by identity only, even if their IdentityWrapper.hashCode() and IdentityWrapper.equals(Object) implement some other semantics.

    A Predicate indicating whether its argument is the same as null.

    A BinaryPredicate that tests if the first integer input argument is less than the second integer input argument.

    A function for converting a list of two elements to a pair.

    A wrapper around a value, so that we can have a final object with a value inside which can be changed.
    Not<T>
    A Predicate negating another.
    NotContainedBy<T>
    A Predicate given a collection on construction that tests if a given object is not contained in the collection when it is applied.
    NotEquals<T>

    Null<A,R>
    A Function that always returns null.
    Or<T>
    A Predicate that is a disjunction of a list of others.
    OrderedPairsOfIntegersIterator
    A cloneable iterator over ordered pairs of integers less than n.
    Pair<T1,T2>
    A pair of objects with hash code and equality reduced to its components.
    PairOf<T>

    ReplaceByIfEqualTo<T>
    A Function constructed on two objects, replaced and replacement.
    SingletonListMaker<T>
    A Function that creates and returns a singleton list from its input argument.
    ToString<T>
    A function for mapping objects to their toString() result.
    Triple<T1,T2,T3>
    A triple of objects with hash code and equality reduced to its components.
    Wrapper<T>
    A wrapper around a value, so that a final wrapper can be used inside a closure (lambda expression) and have its value changed.
